2022-01-19 17:23:43	robbert-vdh	By the way, would adding a `@realtime - nice -19` to bat /etc/security/limits.d/99-realtime-privileges.conf make sense? PipeWire tries setting thread niceness in its realtime module(s)
2022-01-19 17:24:00	robbert-vdh	I now have my own very nice /etc/security/limits.d/99-nice.conf
2022-01-19 17:26:23	dvzrv	robbert-vdh: maybe? I was always under the impression, that it is not really required (nice level), but I also only have questionable halfknowledge about everything
2022-01-19 17:26:25	dvzrv	haha
2022-01-19 17:27:02	robbert-vdh	Yeah I too never really touch niceness so idk either
2022-01-19 17:27:10	dvzrv	robbert-vdh: do you see any error messages somewhere?
2022-01-19 17:27:19	dvzrv	we could as wtay about it
2022-01-19 17:28:32	robbert-vdh	In PipeWire you do if you doo't have permissions to use it. I think wtay wants to always use rtkit for that but it's a bit weird because RTKit doesn't just set niceness, it will change the scheduling policy to SCHED_OTHER|SCHED_RESET_ON_FORK and _then_ change niceness
2022-01-19 17:29:16	robbert-vdh	PipeWire tries to use set the niceness to -11 on the main thread
2022-01-19 17:32:34	robbert-vdh	dvzrv: `journalctl --user -u pipewire | rg 'could not set nice-level' | count`
2022-01-19 17:32:42	robbert-vdh	166 entries :D
2022-01-19 17:33:26	robbert-vdh	That's mostly why I gave myself permissions to do that. Doubt it actually makes a big difference in practice
2022-01-19 17:35:22	dvzrv	robbert-vdh: hmm, I don't have that on my machine. do you have a specific configuration for pipewire?
2022-01-19 17:35:59	dvzrv	robbert-vdh: I think realtime-privileges is also not yet an optional dependency for pipewire (but should be)
2022-01-19 17:36:02	robbert-vdh	dvzrv: If you're using module-rtkit then it will use RTKit instead of setpriority()
2022-01-19 17:36:42	robbert-vdh	Next update will only have a single module-rt, and it will use RTKit if you don't have realtime priviliges
2022-01-19 17:36:51	robbert-vdh	So that's one less configuration step
2022-01-19 17:38:40	dvzrv	robbert-vdh: ah, I understand
2022-01-19 17:38:42	dvzrv	hmm
2022-01-19 17:39:03	dvzrv	if only that wouldn't require polkit :S
2022-01-19 17:41:29	dvzrv	wow, I was not aware, that heftig is now the rtkit upstream: https://github.com/heftig/rtkit
2022-01-19 17:42:14	dvzrv	hm, rtkit module should be on by default and I still don't see those errors
2022-01-19 17:42:44	dvzrv	maybe my services are not verbose enough?
2022-01-19 17:44:10	robbert-vdh	dvzrv: No you won't see the error _because_ you're using rtkit
2022-01-19 17:44:36	robbert-vdh	rtkit runs as root, so it can do all of those things without any additional config
2022-01-19 17:45:53	dvzrv	robbert-vdh: ahh, I misunderstood you then
2022-01-19 17:45:58	robbert-vdh	If you don't use RTKit (so module-rt with PipeWire <=0.3.43, module-rt+realtime priviliges with PipeWire >0.3.44) then you'll get that error if your user can't set the niceness that low
2022-01-19 17:46:33	dvzrv	alright
